<div class="card">
  <h2>Terms of Use</h2>
  <p>Welcome to NPL. These Terms of Use govern your access and use of the NPL anonymous messaging service.</p>
  <h3>Anonymous messaging rules</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>No harassment, threats, hate speech, or illegal content.</li>
    <li>Do not attempt to deanonymize senders.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>User responsibilities</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Keep your account secure. Choose a strong password.</li>
    <li>Comply with local laws.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Abuse prevention</h3>
  <p>We implement rate limits, IP hashing, and content moderation filters. Repeat abuse may lead to termination.</p>
  <h3>Account termination</h3>
  <p>We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate terms.</p>
  <h3>Liability limitations</h3>
  <p>We provide the service "as is" and disclaim warranties to the maximum extent permitted.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>We collect minimal data needed to provide the service. This includes email for authentication, uploaded profile photos, message content stored anonymously, and payment records for purchases.</p>
  <h3>Data collection</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Account information: username, email, password (hashed).</li>
    <li>Profile photos: stored for display.</li>
    <li>Messages: text and hashed sender IP only.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Cookies</h3>
  <p>We use cookies for sessions and CSRF protection.</p>
  <h3>Authentication</h3>
  <p>Passwords are hashed with bcrypt. Google OAuth may be used for convenience.</p>
  <h3>Payments</h3>
  <p>We store minimal payment records and use Paystack for payment processing.</p>
  <h3>User rights</h3>
  <p>Users can request deletion of their account and data.</p>
</div>